The paper is about improving query suggestion in search engines, which is a task related to information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed model uses a sequence-to-sequence approach with attention and copy mechanisms, which are common techniques in natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also proposes new evaluation metrics for generative models, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of deep learning techniques such as sequence-to-sequence models and attention mechanisms suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the deep learning community (cs.DL).
